2300 Volney Rd, Youngstown, OH 44511
$30,000, 5 bd, 4 ba, 3,624 sqft

Located just around the corner from beautiful Mill Creek Park, this home is fixer upper's dream with endless potential. Private side entrance provides possibility for third floor apartment in addition to spacious main house living area. This property is for sale by deed in escrow. Once an offer is accepted, buyer will have 180 days to complete required repairs as outlined by seller in application before deed can be transferred. Buyer must show proof of funds/financing for both the acquisition and rehabilitation costs associated with this property prior to making an offer.

Listing courtesy of:
Branches Real Estate
Tiffany Sokol

node.text:
714 S Broadway St, Leavenworth, KS 66048
$745,000, 5 bd, 5 ba, 7,681 sqft

One of, if not THE MOST MAJESTIC,  historic homes in Leavenworth, this wonderfully preserved 1885 jewel, is available and just waiting for a new family to love and enjoy it.  Boasting nearly 8000 square feet of pure authenticity, you will be impressed from the moment you enter the huge foyer, offering intricate woodwork, beautiful ceiling detail, and open staircases to second level, which offers 5 bedrooms and 4 baths, including the servants' quarters and backstaircase to the kitchen.  Third level is one, huge, open space, most probably the original ballroom, but lending itself to endless possibilities...maybe an upstairs family room, office, craft area, or maybe all of those at once...it's huge! The grounds encompass just over 6 acres, which features a lovely patio area, and of course the detached garage/original carriage house which provides tons of space for vehicles, wokshop, whatever you can imagine!

Listing Provided by:
Karen Hill
Coldwell Banker Reilly & Sons

David Thiel
Coldwell Banker Reilly & Sons

node.text:
901 Colonial Ave, Norfolk, VA 23507
$650,000, 7 bd, 5 ba, 4,710 sqft

Impressive Victorian situated on corner lot in historic Ghent. A history lover's dream, this stately home features all brick exterior complete w turret, tiger oak woodwork, beveled glass mirrors,& authentic Victorian craftsmanship. The grand foyer is flanked by dual parlors w original pocket doors & ornamental fps.  Expansive formal dining room w/ coffered ceiling. Spacious Kitchen w butler's pantry, private study, & powder room complete first level. Second level: 4 bedrooms 2 full baths & spa room. Third level: 3 bedrooms, walk-in closet, attic storage. Basement: 3 rms & Laundry. Exterior: front & side porch, deck. No Flood Ins Req.

Open House
Sun, Sep 19
12:00 PM - 2:00 PM

Listed by:
Bobby Lawrence
BHHS Towne Realty

Katie Howlett
BHHS Towne Realty

node.text:
110 W Gaston St, Savannah, GA 31401
$2,950,000, 6 bd, 7 ba, 7,912 sqft

This magnificent freestanding Italianate Victorian home is perfectly positioned on Gaston Street in Savannah’s Landmark District, steps from Forsyth Park & Bull Street. Originally built for Confederate Capt. Nathan B. Brown in 1874 & featured in the movie “Savannah,” this grand home offers the ultimate in Savannah style, plus elevator access to all floors & 3-car attached garage. Discover stunning period details, bay windows, exceptional millwork, elegant parlors, inlaid parquet floors, arched doorways, 14-foot ceilings & 3 covered side porches. Surrounded by wrought iron fencing & ideal for entertaining, this lovely home boasts a grand parlor with bay windows, fireplace, pocket doors, crystal chandeliers & access to the covered side porch via original Italianate doors. A renovated chef’s kitchen has stainless steel appliances, granite countertops & an open design with a spacious sitting area, brick fireplace & English pub-style bar. Income-producing garden apartment, workshop & more.

Listed by:
Staci M Donegan
Seabolt Brokers LLC
